description:
Loretta Lynn: Still a Mountain Girl

Arts Documentary hosted by Vikram Jayanti, published by BBC broadcasted as part of BBC Arena series in 2016 - English narration. 
http://docuwiki.net/images/2/2f/Loretta-Lynn-Still-a-Mountain-Girl-Cover.jpg

Information
------------------------------
Legendary country music singer-songwriter Loretta Lynn is loved by fans from across the world. She has sold over 45 million albums worldwide and won more awards than any other female country music star. With affectionate and irreverent contributions from her extended family of self-confessed rednecks, now in her early eighties and still going strong, Loretta looks back at her long and extraordinary life, from being born a coal miner's daughter in Kentucky to receiving the Presidential Medal of Freedom from Barack Obama in 2013. Featuring Willie Nelson, Sheryl Crow, Jack White, Sissy Spacek and Loretta herself.
